The '''Anti-Communist League of the Caribbean''' ({{lang-es|Legión Anticomunista del Caribe}}, LAC), also known as the '''Anti-Communist Legion of the Caribbean''', was an anti-[[Castroism|Castroist]] [[right-wing politics|right-wing]] group based in the [[Dominican Republic]]<ref name="Nordlinger">{{cite news |last=Nordlinger |first=Jay |authorlink=Jay Nordlinger |date=September 19, 2013 |title= More from the Anti-Che  |url=http://www.nationalreview.com/article/358877/more-anti-che-jay-nordlinger |newspaper=National Review Online |location= |publisher= |accessdate=June 23, 2014}}</ref> funded by the dictators [[Rafael Trujillo]] of the [[Dominican Republic]], [[Anastasio Somoza Debayle|Anastasio Somoza]] of Nicaragua and former Cuban Secret Police Chief Orlando Piedra.<ref name=Scott-1>[[Peter Dale Scott|Scott, Peter Dale]] (1993) ''Deep Politics and the Death of JFK'', University of California Press, p. 88</ref>  The purpose of the group was to overthrow the government of [[Fidel Castro]] in Cuba. The group eventually became part of the [[World Anti-Communist League]] in 1967.

The group was made up of Spaniards, Cubans, Croatians, Germans, Greeks and right-wing mercenaries trained in the Dominican Republic.<ref name=Anderson>[[Jon Lee Anderson|Anderson, Jon Lee]] (1997). Che Guevara: A Revolutionary Life. New York: Grove Press. {{ISBN|0-8021-1600-0}}. p 435</ref> The group staged a failed attempt to overthrow Castro in 1959.<ref name=Crassweller>Robert D. Crassweller. Trujillo: The Life and Times of a Caribbean Dictator. MacMillan, New York (1966) p. 351</ref>{{Verify source|date=June 2014}}

The headquarters of the Anti-Communist League was at one time located at [[Guy Banister]]'s New Orleans office.<ref name=JFK-1>https://archive.org/details/For_The_Record_288_Update_on_the_JFK_Assassination</ref> The same location appeared on [[Fair Play for Cuba Committee]] leaflets distributed by Lee Harvey Oswald and such references to the league are often made in texts concerning [[John F. Kennedy assassination conspiracy theories|conspiracy theories relating to Kennedy assassination]].

